-- U.S. Stocks Fluctuate; Hewlett-Packard Climbs as Forecast Beats Estimates
-- B y   M i c h a e l   P .   R e g a n
-- 2010-09-29T16:25:47Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-29/u-s-stocks-fluctuate-hewlett-packard-climbs-as-forecast-beats-estimates.html
U.S. stocks fluctuated as energy
companies rose on higher oil prices and Hewlett-Packard Co.
surged after its profit forecast topped estimates, helping the
market recover from an early slide.  Schlumberger Ltd. and Chevron Corp. paced gains in 36 of 39
energy companies in the Standard & Poor’s 500 Index as oil
rallied as much as 2.2 percent. Hewlett-Packard jumped 2.6
percent for the top advance in the Dow Jones Industrial Average
after also announcing plans to return cash to shareholders.  The S&P 500 increased less than 0.1 percent to 1,147.71 at
12:22 p.m. in New York after tumbling as much as 0.7 percent.
The Dow climbed 3.02 points, or less than 0.1 percent, to
10,861.16 after sliding 56 points earlier.  Earlier losses came amid concern Europe’s sovereign debt
crisis will worsen as workers in Spain interrupted
transportation and broadcasts to protest cuts in government
spending.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
